# Demo status badge

Every `README.md` under `artifacts/demos/aap-demo-*/` **must** include a `Status` badge as the **first** badge in the badge row (before AAP, CasC, platform, or any other badge).

## Required values

| State | Badge Markdown | When to use |
|---|---|---|
| Work in progress | `![Status](https://img.shields.io/badge/Status-WIP-yellow)` | Demo is incomplete, untested, or not yet validated end-to-end |
| Ready | `![Status](https://img.shields.io/badge/Status-Ready-brightgreen)` | Demo has been tested and is ready to run live with a customer |

## Placement rule

The Status badge must appear on the **first badge line**, before any other badge:

```markdown
![Status](https://img.shields.io/badge/Status-WIP-yellow)
![Red Hat AAP](https://img.shields.io/badge/AAP-2.7+-red)
![CasC](https://img.shields.io/badge/CasC-infra.aap__configuration-blue)
```

Do **not** place the Status badge after other badges or on a separate line.

## Rules

- Default state for new demos is **WIP**. Change to **Ready** only when the demo has been validated end-to-end.
- The badge label is always `Status` (no spaces, no alternate capitalization).
- Use only the two states above; do not introduce intermediate states (e.g. `Beta`, `Testing`).
- When creating or scaffolding a new `aap-demo-*` artifact, always insert the WIP badge as the first line of the badge block.
- When a demo is declared ready for live delivery, update the badge to `Ready`; do not remove it.

## Out of scope

- Non-demo artifacts (labs, workshops, scripts) — this badge is not required outside `artifacts/demos/aap-demo-*/`.
- The shields.io style parameter — use the default style (no `?style=` suffix).
